That we'd line up guests here

01:30.525 --> 01:32.532
and they would sort
of sage you and Lars.

01:32.557 --> 01:33.797
Saging's a little bit basic.

01:33.822 --> 01:35.297
Y-Yeah. Yeah, that is basic.

01:35.322 --> 01:36.705
So, maybe we won't do that, but like...

01:36.729 --> 01:38.313
But I feel like no one's basic anymore.

01:38.338 --> 01:39.594
- Yeah.
- Like, let's be basic.

01:39.619 --> 01:41.134
Yeah, and so, I was thinking
we should be basic.

01:41.158 --> 01:42.594
- And so... Yeah.
- God.

01:42.619 --> 01:45.407
I mean, this place, it's just so...

01:45.432 --> 01:46.993
It... It's like...

01:47.018 --> 01:48.314
- ... real.
- ... real.

01:48.339 --> 01:49.539
- You know?
- Yeah.

01:49.564 --> 01:51.784
And, like, he's so...

01:51.943 --> 01:53.244
American and cool.

01:53.269 --> 01:54.749
- Oh, yeah.
- Jacob. I'm Jacob.

01:54.774 --> 01:56.252
Jacob, I love your outfit.

01:56.277 --> 01:58.308
- Ja... What... What's happening?
- It's Jacob.

01:58.333 --> 01:59.357
You can just go with it.

01:59.381 --> 02:00.980
- And this is Rudy.
- Oh, my God.

02:01.005 --> 02:02.652
- Oh, my God.
- Rudy, this is Sierra.

02:02.677 --> 02:04.558
I think that you are the unkempt man

02:04.583 --> 02:05.637
who lives in the barn, right?

02:05.661 --> 02:07.488
You're the littlest person
I've ever met.

02:07.513 --> 02:09.449
- It's an honor.
- Okay, total sidebar...

02:09.473 --> 02:12.175
Can I just say you
have an exquisite body?

02:12.742 --> 02:13.742
You may.

02:13.767 --> 02:15.355
I'm so glad someone finally said it.

02:15.380 --> 02:17.433
I've been thinking it
the whole time here.

02:17.458 --> 02:18.938
- Guys.
- Hey.

02:18.963 --> 02:22.316
Okay, this is the local ensemble team

02:22.341 --> 02:24.090
that is going to bring
your wedding to fruition,

02:24.114 --> 02:26.019
and this is Sierra.

02:26.044 --> 02:28.855
I am absolutely teeming with gratitude

02:28.880 --> 02:30.273
for your guidance and nourishment

02:30.298 --> 02:32.347
as I make this transition
into my married life.

02:32.372 --> 02:33.403
- Yeah.
- You know,

02:33.428 --> 02:35.520
my dear friend Marianne Williamson

02:35.545 --> 02:37.528
just said some wise words to me...

02:37.553 --> 02:38.911
"Love is like a book,

02:38.936 --> 02:41.543
and I appreciate you helping
me writing this next chapter."

02:41.568 --> 02:43.372
- That's really sweet.
- Oh, wow.

02:43.397 --> 02:45.661
This is why she's the best, you guys.

02:46.263 --> 02:47.856
I follow you on Instagram.

02:47.881 --> 02:49.536
You never respond to my messages.

02:49.561 --> 02:51.715
Oh, I don't handle my messages.

02:51.740 --> 02:53.271
You have to talk to Katsana about that.

02:53.295 --> 02:54.848
Oh. Um, okay.

02:54.873 --> 02:57.180
So, let's just do introductions.
Obviously, I'm Rio.

02:57.205 --> 02:59.145
I'm the best friend.
I'm the wedding planner.

02:59.170 --> 03:01.489
- I'm whatever... mother of pigs.
- She does it all.

03:01.514 --> 03:03.287
Should we... Do you want to...
Clara, do you want to...

03:03.311 --> 03:06.444
Um, I'm Clara. I am a Pisces,

03:06.469 --> 03:09.217
and I will be making your
22-tiered wedding cake.

03:09.242 --> 03:11.155
Oh. Um, did you...

03:11.180 --> 03:13.413
So, 20 two-tiered cakes.

03:13.438 --> 03:14.531
Yeah, we're saying the same thing.

03:14.555 --> 03:17.030
I don't think we are.
So... What did you say?

03:17.055 --> 03:20.811
- Twenty two...
- 22-tiered wedding cake.

03:22.158 --> 03:23.381
Great. Okay.

03:23.406 --> 03:24.827
And Jacob, you're on decor.

03:24.852 --> 03:27.226
You're gonna be doing the
thousand origami cranes.

03:27.414 --> 03:30.296
If all I can do is fold paper,
how come this?

03:30.597 --> 03:32.678
But you're good for origami cranes?

03:32.703 --> 03:34.007
Yeah, yeah. I can fold the cranes.

03:34.031 --> 03:35.554
Okay. Um, alright.

03:35.579 --> 03:36.956
Here's another thing that
we should discuss,

03:36.980 --> 03:38.514
which is the father-daughter dance.

03:38.539 --> 03:39.758
Like, what do you want to do?

03:39.783 --> 03:40.968
It's obviously a unique situation.

03:40.992 --> 03:43.116
You have two dads... Daddy and Pop-Pop.

03:43.141 --> 03:45.535
Like, do you want to dance
with them at the same time?

03:45.560 --> 03:46.952
You know what? I am feeling...

03:46.977 --> 03:49.405
I'm feeling a little deluged right now.

03:49.430 --> 03:50.436
- Okay.
- You know?

03:50.461 --> 03:52.069
Why don't we open a bottle of champagne?

03:52.094 --> 03:53.545
Sure. And so...

03:53.570 --> 03:56.178
I feel like we should, like,
finish the meeting first, right?

03:56.203 --> 03:57.491
And then we can do champagne?

03:57.516 --> 04:01.116
Ooh, sounds like Rio's putting
the "snore" in "Bucksnort."

04:05.328 --> 04:07.217
- She got... That's...
- Okay, okay.

04:07.242 --> 04:08.475
- Very funny.
- I love it.

04:08.500 --> 04:10.037
- I love it.
- She's very funny.

04:10.062 --> 04:12.764
Oh, hey, Brandon,
where do you guys keep cannons

04:12.789 --> 04:14.303
for shooting, like, rose petals?

04:14.328 --> 04:16.504
Come on, man.
We don't even have shampoo.

04:16.529 --> 04:17.616
- Oh.
- Brandon!

04:17.641 --> 04:19.709
Is that Mike? I need to talk to him.

04:19.733 --> 04:22.616
Hey, bud, be careful.
She is on a war path right now.

04:22.641 --> 04:25.084
She already ticketed three
people for jaywalking.

04:25.109 --> 04:26.428
We don't even have a crosswalk.

04:26.453 --> 04:27.975
- Okay, okay.
- Mike.

04:28.000 --> 04:31.131
I noticed that you placed a
very large order of alcohol.

04:31.156 --> 04:32.843
Now, you know you can't
serve that at a wedding...

04:32.867 --> 04:34.116
... without a liquor license.

04:34.141 --> 04:35.546
We don't need a license for that, do we?

04:35.570 --> 04:37.233
I mean, it's... It's not on my list.

04:37.258 --> 04:38.702
- Let me see that.
- Well, you know,

04:38.727 --> 04:39.889
I need that back. Okay?

04:39.914 --> 04:41.507
So, you're having the
wedding at Rudy's barn?

04:41.531 --> 04:42.553
Is he okay with that?

04:42.578 --> 04:43.750
- Yeah. Yeah.
- They... They're not

04:43.774 --> 04:44.959
speaking right now.

04:44.984 --> 04:46.881
- Oh.
- Okay, we got butterflies... no.

04:46.906 --> 04:48.366
Fireworks... nope.

04:48.391 --> 04:50.077
I'm denying your wedding permit.

04:50.102 --> 04:52.108
Wait, did we even apply for a permit?

04:52.133 --> 04:53.233
No. Would you like one?

04:53.258 --> 04:54.444
Uh... sure.

04:54.469 --> 04:55.959
Denied!

04:57.843 --> 04:59.358
Okay, so, this clearly

04:59.383 --> 05:00.709
has something to do with the breakup.

05:00.733 --> 05:02.545
- 100%. Definitely.
- Yeah.

05:02.570 --> 05:03.875
But I'm not gonna be
the one to tell her.

05:03.899 --> 05:05.156
- Are you kidding me?
- Listen, I can't have

05:05.180 --> 05:07.295
your mom on full tilt for this wedding.

05:07.320 --> 05:08.538
So, we've got to figure out

05:08.563 --> 05:10.398
how to cool things down
between Constance and Rudy.

05:10.422 --> 05:11.506
Yeah, we... we just got to

05:11.531 --> 05:12.851
figure out a way to break
the seal, right?

05:12.875 --> 05:14.789
- Uh-huh, uh-huh, uh-huh.
- Create some conversation.

05:14.813 --> 05:17.131
- There we go.
- Help them move past this.

05:17.156 --> 05:18.609
Yes, and we got to fast-track it.

05:18.633 --> 05:19.889
Brandon, watch the register.

05:19.914 --> 05:21.803
- I'm gonna go tase someone.
- Alright.

05:21.828 --> 05:22.992
Theresa, I know I've been getting

05:23.016 --> 05:25.077
a lot of comments on my body lately,

05:25.102 --> 05:26.959
but I'd appreciate your brutal honesty.

05:27.518 --> 05:29.624
- You're just jealous.
- Hey.

05:29.649 --> 05:31.811
Rudy, I-I was hoping to talk to you

05:31.836 --> 05:33.670
for a second about Constance.

05:33.695 --> 05:34.772
We had a clean break.

05:34.797 --> 05:36.538
Cold turkey's the only
way to stop anything.

05:36.563 --> 05:38.420
Six years ago,
I stopped making left turns.

05:38.445 --> 05:39.639
Haven't done one since.

05:39.664 --> 05:40.834
So, h-how then do you...

05:40.859 --> 05:42.733
- Three rights, Mike.
- Fascinating.

05:42.821 --> 05:46.491
Uh, just to bring it back
to Connie, she...

05:47.152 --> 05:50.590
asked i-if she could
get a recipe from you.

05:50.615 --> 05:53.052
What recipe? She knows
the only thing I make is trail mix.

05:53.077 --> 05:56.178
Uh-huh. She wants to know your
peanut-to-almond proportions.

05:56.203 --> 05:57.686
So, uh, she's on her way...

05:57.711 --> 05:59.334
- On her way now?
- Yeah. She'll be here.

05:59.359 --> 06:00.350
- On her way.
- Maybe we could regroup

06:00.375 --> 06:01.397
in, like, 30 minutes?

06:01.422 --> 06:03.757
Great. I look forward to
telling her my nut ratio.

06:05.828 --> 06:07.092
Yeah. It's just...

06:07.117 --> 06:09.014
You have a weird smile on your face.

06:09.039 --> 06:10.655
- No, I really don't.
- Okay.

06:10.680 --> 06:11.703
Well, look...

06:11.727 --> 06:14.350
I've got to find a place to
rent a chuppah in Nebraska,

06:14.375 --> 06:16.616
which is quite a challenge,
but I'll see you shortly?

06:16.641 --> 06:18.194
- Okay.
- Okay.

06:19.459 --> 06:21.452
Wait, Rio, do you remember
when we threw the rave

06:21.477 --> 06:23.328
in the Meatpacking District,
and I got salmonella?

06:23.352 --> 06:26.186
- How could I forget?
- Oh, my God. We were rolling so hard.

06:26.211 --> 06:27.516
It was ridiculous.

06:27.541 --> 06:29.577
My God, are you guys
talking about drugs?

06:29.602 --> 06:31.756
I lost my virginity on Ibuprofen.

06:31.781 --> 06:33.522
Ooh. Did you wait for it to kick in?

06:33.547 --> 06:35.006
I didn't think of that.

06:35.031 --> 06:36.405
Are you guys carrying right now?

06:36.430 --> 06:39.374
Because, like, if you were
to totally peer-pressure me,

06:39.399 --> 06:40.741
- I would do it.
- We're not doing drugs.

06:40.765 --> 06:42.990
Okay, well, look,
if you want to get a little loopy...

06:43.015 --> 06:44.444
I have got some horse tranquilizers.

06:44.468 --> 06:45.912
- Oh, my God. Kent.
- Ooh.

06:45.937 --> 06:48.850
Kent coming in hot with suggestions.

06:49.233 --> 06:50.843
You're not gonna like
how they're administered.

06:50.867 --> 06:52.505
Horse tranquilizers... Oh, wait.

06:52.530 --> 06:54.326
- Hey.
- What do you have?

06:54.351 --> 06:57.061
I have wedding planning. Come on.

06:57.086 --> 06:58.631
Can we focus on that later?

07:01.728 --> 07:03.412
Come on, Rio. You really have changed.

07:03.437 --> 07:04.718
I mean, I'm telling you,
she used to be fun.

07:04.742 --> 07:05.895
Now it's just like...

07:05.919 --> 07:07.311
You know? It's like downhill.

07:07.336 --> 07:09.056
- Like, what happened?
- I'm still fun.

07:09.526 --> 07:10.993
- No.
- I still have fun.

07:11.018 --> 07:13.236
I throw down. I throw down a lot.

07:13.261 --> 07:17.415
If you throw down,
why don't we throw a par-tay tonight?

07:17.440 --> 07:18.964
- Oh.
- Like we used to, right?

07:18.989 --> 07:20.861
- Yeah, yeah.
- Totally debauched bacchanal.

07:20.886 --> 07:24.095
- Oh, here? Here?
- Like a full-blown rave.

07:24.120 --> 07:26.907
- What do you think? Are you down?
- I think... I think yes. Yes!

07:26.932 --> 07:28.603
Yes! Right?

07:29.959 --> 07:32.266
- Annihilation!
- Yes!

07:32.291 --> 07:34.307
- Take it down, take it down!
- There we go. There's the Rio I know!

07:34.331 --> 07:37.454
Yes! Yes! Get it! Yes, yes, yes!

07:37.479 --> 07:38.931
- Mm!
- Oh. Are you okay?

07:38.956 --> 07:39.993
It's just... Uh... Th...

07:40.018 --> 07:41.782
There's a lot more in
there than I imagined.

07:41.807 --> 07:44.581
Brandon said that Rudy
wanted me to meet him here

07:44.606 --> 07:45.956
because of what?

07:45.981 --> 07:46.986
W-What again?

07:47.011 --> 07:48.970
He saw a large naked man walking by,

07:48.995 --> 07:50.867
and he made a citizen's arrest,

07:50.892 --> 07:53.415
but the man escaped because
he was covered in oil,

07:53.440 --> 07:56.162
and now Rudy wants
to do a police sketch.

07:56.664 --> 07:58.280
That's too much. That's way too much.

07:58.304 --> 07:59.311
W-W-Wait, wait, wait.

07:59.336 --> 08:01.732
He said he was gonna
be waiting for me here?

08:01.757 --> 08:02.929
Is that what you... I don't see him.

08:02.953 --> 08:04.351
That... That could be my fault.

08:04.375 --> 08:05.733
I-I might have got the time wrong.

08:05.757 --> 08:07.194
But I'm sure he just
stepped out for a second.

08:07.218 --> 08:08.219
- He'll be right back.
- Yeah.

08:08.243 --> 08:10.170
You know,
this is such a waste of my time.

08:10.195 --> 08:12.428
I could have been
setting up a speed trap.

08:12.460 --> 08:14.780
This is so stupid.

08:14.805 --> 08:16.323
What the hell, Mike?

08:16.348 --> 08:18.666
Come on. I held up
my end of the bargain.

08:20.207 --> 08:21.807
What's this? W-What is it...

08:21.832 --> 08:23.917
What do you got on
your neck here, Theresa?

08:26.143 --> 08:27.706
Okay...

08:27.731 --> 08:30.159
"Sorry, but I can't talk to Constance.

08:30.184 --> 08:34.073
I've gone into my underground bunker...

08:34.097 --> 08:37.222
for two to five years,
depending on how hungry I am.

08:37.246 --> 08:40.025
Please take care of Theresa,
and don't try to find me.

08:40.049 --> 08:42.197
Love, Rudy."

08:42.222 --> 08:43.361
