- Hey!
- Rio!

10:07.834 --> 10:09.443
What a dope milieu!

10:09.468 --> 10:10.768
Yes.

10:10.963 --> 10:12.684
Yeah, so dope!

10:12.709 --> 10:14.591
So dope! I love it!

10:14.616 --> 10:17.272
Rio, everyone has hands!

10:17.297 --> 10:19.473
- We...
- We all have hands!

10:19.498 --> 10:21.195
Yeah!

10:21.524 --> 10:23.498
I did drugs!

10:27.266 --> 10:28.350
- Rio!
- Oh, hi.

10:28.375 --> 10:30.911
I just saw Rudy crawling
on the ground like a cat.

10:30.936 --> 10:33.084
What are you chewing?
Clara, what are you chewing?

10:33.109 --> 10:34.327
I told you not to chew any
more of those gummies.

10:34.351 --> 10:35.484
Are you chewing those gummies?

10:35.508 --> 10:36.787
- Clara.
- Oh, I should take my top off.

10:36.811 --> 10:37.873
No, I didn't say that.

10:37.898 --> 10:39.569
You know what? Just stay with me here.

10:39.594 --> 10:41.061
Now hold. Look at this hand.

10:41.086 --> 10:43.381
Stay with me. You're watching my fist.

10:43.413 --> 10:45.560
You're watching my fi... Water.

10:45.585 --> 10:47.928
- Wow!
- Go and take it outside.

10:47.953 --> 10:49.623
This is awesome.

10:49.648 --> 10:51.076
Oh, God. Hello.

10:51.101 --> 10:53.514
Yes. Hi. Who is that guy?

10:53.539 --> 10:55.366
I think he follows me on Insta.

10:55.391 --> 10:57.639
- And that got him here somehow?
- Eh, you know what?

10:57.664 --> 11:00.826
I posted about the barn,
so maybe he saw my location tag.

11:00.851 --> 11:02.026
Oh, wow.

11:02.594 --> 11:04.983
- Oh, that's...
- Oh, my God.

11:05.499 --> 11:07.873
- Come on, guys!
- I-I... Oh.

11:08.944 --> 11:10.991
Another cow bone.

11:11.016 --> 11:12.233
How many does that make?

11:12.258 --> 11:14.241
Enough to make nine full cows.

11:14.266 --> 11:15.485
Whoop, whoop!

11:15.510 --> 11:18.513
Get your hands in the
air and drop your bone!

11:19.327 --> 11:20.676
Hey, Ma.

11:20.701 --> 11:22.772
I was just helping Mike mow his land.

11:22.797 --> 11:26.014
Don't fix your mouth to lie when
I got a megaphone in my hand.

11:26.433 --> 11:27.889
What the hell is going on?

11:27.914 --> 11:30.176
Mike came up with some crazy idea

11:30.201 --> 11:31.897
about getting you and Rudy to talk.

11:31.922 --> 11:33.959
But I said, "No, Mike. That's not right.

11:33.984 --> 11:35.186
This is none of our business."

11:35.211 --> 11:36.584
I... W... Really?

11:36.609 --> 11:39.592
Yeah. Rudy went down into his bunker

11:39.617 --> 11:42.600
because I suggested that you
guys have a conversation.

11:42.625 --> 11:44.709
Rudy went into his bunker?

11:44.734 --> 11:46.662
Yes. D... Has he told you where it is?

11:46.687 --> 11:47.826
No, he didn't tell me.

11:47.851 --> 11:49.975
Don't worry, Mom. This is Mike's mess.

11:50.000 --> 11:51.217
Just Mike.

11:51.242 --> 11:52.334
But I'm-a help you fix it.

11:52.359 --> 11:54.319
You are such a good son, Brandon.

11:54.344 --> 11:55.370
We raised you right.

11:55.395 --> 11:57.311
But you, on the other hand...

11:57.336 --> 11:59.076
Why didn't you just leave us alone?

11:59.101 --> 12:01.248
Well, I would have loved
to have left you alone,

12:01.273 --> 12:03.655
but one of you lives in my barn

12:03.680 --> 12:05.108
and mopes around all day long,

12:05.133 --> 12:07.025
and then I bump into you,
and you've got a long face.

12:07.049 --> 12:08.659
So I know this isn't going so well,

12:08.684 --> 12:09.984
you cutting him out of your life.

12:10.008 --> 12:13.928
So, you're gonna force two
adults who just broke up

12:13.953 --> 12:15.037
to be friends

12:15.062 --> 12:17.631
so that you can get out of
getting a liquor license?

12:17.656 --> 12:19.647
When you phrase it that way, sure,

12:19.672 --> 12:21.350
it does sound a little insincere.

12:21.375 --> 12:23.225
I-It's just awkward between us.

12:23.250 --> 12:26.131
I-I don't even know how to
be friends with him again.

12:26.156 --> 12:27.655
Well, I do believe step one

12:27.680 --> 12:30.272
is extracting him
from beneath the earth.

12:30.297 --> 12:31.297
And then what?

12:31.322 --> 12:32.537
You take a little baby step,

12:32.562 --> 12:33.944
and then it leads to another,

12:33.969 --> 12:36.186
- and you move...
- Hey, I found something!

12:36.211 --> 12:37.842
Is it Rudy?

12:42.789 --> 12:45.264
S-Sierra, I wondered
if you could just make, like,

12:45.289 --> 12:46.638
a really chill announcement,

12:46.663 --> 12:49.006
just telling people
not to wreck the farm,

12:49.031 --> 12:51.381
mainly 'cause it's, like,
my livelihood or whatever,

12:51.406 --> 12:53.249
and, you know,
it just has gotten a little bit bigger

12:53.273 --> 12:55.145
than I initially thought it would.

12:55.170 --> 12:58.178
Look, I'm sorry for putting
the party on Instagram.

12:58.706 --> 13:01.256
I just wanted my family to
see me having a good time,

13:01.281 --> 13:02.593
and I thought they
would change their minds

13:02.617 --> 13:03.920
about not coming to the wedding.

13:03.945 --> 13:05.381
Uh, what?

13:05.406 --> 13:07.342
What do you mean, your family's
not coming to the wedding?

13:07.366 --> 13:09.150
Daddy totally despises Lars.

13:09.175 --> 13:10.686
Whatever. Do you want more moonshine?

13:10.711 --> 13:11.991
No, I don't want more moonshine.

13:12.016 --> 13:13.413
I want to talk to you about why Daddy

13:13.437 --> 13:14.515
doesn't want to come to your wedding.

13:14.539 --> 13:16.123
Yes, but Kent's about to jump

13:16.148 --> 13:17.889
from really high up for no reason.

13:17.914 --> 13:20.678
- Kent is what?
- Who wants to see me jump, baby?!

13:22.930 --> 13:25.320
No, no! Not... No, Kent!

13:25.345 --> 13:28.186
I need a landing zone!
Get that hay in here!

13:28.211 --> 13:29.444
Sierra, Sierra, listen.

13:29.469 --> 13:31.056
It's a really big deal,
what you're saying.

13:31.080 --> 13:32.984
I-I want to talk to you.
That's what I'm here for.

13:33.008 --> 13:34.507
- Look! over here!
- What is it?

13:34.531 --> 13:37.998
Oh, my God! Guys! Door in the floor!

13:38.023 --> 13:40.200
You're avoiding me right now.

13:40.225 --> 13:44.193
Door in the floor! Door in the floor!

13:53.609 --> 13:55.685
Barn man!

14:03.452 --> 14:05.341
What is it? More cow bones?

14:05.366 --> 14:07.709
It's Clarabones.

14:08.734 --> 14:10.740
Clara, are you okay, girl? What...

14:10.765 --> 14:12.599
Oh, yeah. I ate all these gummies,

14:12.624 --> 14:14.302
and then I saw Rudy
crawling in the barn,

14:14.327 --> 14:15.873
and then all these people showed up,

14:15.898 --> 14:18.292
- and I was like, "nap before orgy."
- W-W-Wait.

14:18.317 --> 14:19.466
- You saw Rudy?
- Yeah.

14:19.491 --> 14:21.058
- In the barn?
- You two dummies

14:21.083 --> 14:24.357
did not check underneath
Rudy's barn first?

14:25.027 --> 14:27.067
Wow, this is incredible.

14:30.038 --> 14:31.802
Oh, wow. Wow, wow, wow.

14:37.124 --> 14:39.302
Sierra, what is going on?

14:39.327 --> 14:40.999
Why is your family not
coming to your wedding?

14:41.023 --> 14:43.504
Oh, my God. Can you stop? I don't care.

14:43.529 --> 14:45.255
- Neither should you.
- I do care.

14:45.280 --> 14:47.064
I do care. You're hiding here.

14:47.089 --> 14:48.599
- I'm not hiding.
- You're not hiding?

14:48.624 --> 14:50.365
You're literally behind a bunch of cans

14:50.390 --> 14:51.607
in... in an underground bunker

14:51.632 --> 14:53.810
in the middle of Bucksnort, Nebraska.

14:53.835 --> 14:55.130
- I am fine.
- No.

14:55.155 --> 14:57.723
I am fine. Leave me alone.

14:57.748 --> 15:00.380
You say that you haven't changed,
but you really have.

15:00.405 --> 15:02.591
Yes. I have.

15:02.616 --> 15:03.623
I have changed.

15:03.648 --> 15:04.935
I admit that to you.

15:04.960 --> 15:08.167
I do not want to be in this
underground apocalypse bunker

15:08.192 --> 15:11.170
with a bunch of strangers from
the Internet that I don't know.

15:11.195 --> 15:13.677
Don't look at me like, "Oh,
yeah, I got you," okay?

15:13.702 --> 15:15.920
- There it is.
- I have a farm with my husband.

15:15.945 --> 15:17.146
Yes, we get it.

15:17.171 --> 15:18.865
You own a farm, and I'm just

15:18.890 --> 15:20.677
some dumb party girl from New York.

15:20.702 --> 15:21.951
Sierra, please don't do that.

15:21.976 --> 15:24.201
Excuse me. I'm gonna go get my swerve on

15:24.226 --> 15:26.505
and spank that sexy grandfather clock.

15:29.808 --> 15:32.865
Out of my way! Police business!

15:32.890 --> 15:35.076
Y'all are under arrest!

15:35.101 --> 15:38.061
What in God's name is going on here?

15:38.086 --> 15:39.154
Damn, Rudy!

15:39.179 --> 15:40.873
You all are under arrest,

15:40.898 --> 15:43.521
and your wedding ain't
never gonna happen.

15:43.546 --> 15:45.959
This might be bad timing, but Rudy...

15:45.984 --> 15:47.670
what a bunker!

15:49.766 --> 15:51.740
Alright, it's time for mugshots.

15:52.050 --> 15:53.560
Come on, Rudy.

15:57.411 --> 15:58.804
Great, great, great.

15:59.207 --> 16:01.035
- Great.
- Mm.

16:01.924 --> 16:04.099
I do find it beguiling
that this anteroom

16:04.124 --> 16:05.787
also serves as a penal holding facility.

16:05.812 --> 16:07.792
Oh, my goodness. Can't you
just say that it's cool

16:07.816 --> 16:09.845
- the room also serves as a jail cell?
- Mike...

16:09.870 --> 16:11.370
- ... that's not productive.
- Why do you got to be so hoity-toity...

16:11.394 --> 16:13.299
- ... to break the ice.
- Turn to the left

16:13.510 --> 16:15.315
So, Rudy, how long were you planning

16:15.340 --> 16:17.159
on staying in that damn bunker?

16:17.184 --> 16:18.925
Not sure. It depended on how well

16:18.950 --> 16:21.605
I responded to the taste
of thrice-filtered urine.

16:21.840 --> 16:23.323
And you were gonna stay down there

16:23.348 --> 16:25.034
just because I wanted to talk to you?

16:25.059 --> 16:27.120
Rudy, come on. We can't live like that.

16:27.145 --> 16:29.080
Don't worry.
I wouldn't have lasted long.

16:29.105 --> 16:31.182
Ate most of my snacks in the first hour.

16:31.207 --> 16:32.854
I'm powerless over peanut butter.

16:32.879 --> 16:34.448
Alright. Turn to the right.

16:36.246 --> 16:38.932
The only thing I missed about
the above ground world was you.

16:38.957 --> 16:40.744
Even if we're not speaking...

16:41.052 --> 16:42.955
it's nice to be on the
same side of the dirt.

16:42.980 --> 16:44.690
Well, Mike was trying to rope Brandon

16:44.715 --> 16:47.846
into making us friends again, but...

16:47.871 --> 16:49.682
we'll eventually get there.

16:49.922 --> 16:51.979
I'm just not ready for that yet.

16:52.004 --> 16:53.377
I agree.

16:53.402 --> 16:54.609
May I face you?

16:54.640 --> 16:56.307
Yes, go ahead.

16:57.324 --> 17:00.299
If only there was some way
I knew you were doing okay,

17:00.324 --> 17:02.346
but I didn't have to
see you all the time.

17:04.410 --> 17:06.930
Hope that doesn't mean I have to
join some kind of social media.

17:07.026 --> 17:08.593
Just...

17:19.013 --> 17:21.165
It's a police scanner.

17:21.191 --> 17:23.315
Just turn it on and listen.

17:23.339 --> 17:25.096
You'll hear my voice...

17:26.200 --> 17:29.549
and I'll know that you'll be
listening out there somewhere.

17:30.144 --> 17:32.073
This is wonderful.

17:32.196 --> 17:33.346
Ten-four.

17:33.371 --> 17:35.196
Copy that.

17:36.445 --> 17:38.321
Okay. You know what?

17:38.346 --> 17:40.665
I already tried to force two
other people together today.

17:40.690 --> 17:42.040
It did not go well.

17:42.065 --> 17:43.259
Might as well try it again.

17:43.963 --> 17:46.791
You guys... You can't do this.

17:46.816 --> 17:48.850
You can't do this. You're...
You're not even looking at each other,

17:48.874 --> 17:51.278
you're ignoring each other,
and you're old friends.

17:51.303 --> 17:53.218
Do you know how rare that is?

17:53.298 --> 17:54.659
Everyone changes,

17:54.684 --> 17:57.105
but only a few lucky people
get to have someone there

17:57.130 --> 17:58.740
that witnesses the whole thing.

17:58.765 --> 18:00.167
You want to lose that?

18:00.192 --> 18:04.683
You're gonna throw all that
away over some fatuous dispute?

18:05.859 --> 18:08.386
Oh, that's right, sister.
I know some long words, too.

18:08.919 --> 18:10.784
Don't do that.

18:15.237 --> 18:16.803
Sierra...

18:17.135 --> 18:18.722
back in the day,

18:18.747 --> 18:21.594
we would go out, and we'd... party

18:21.619 --> 18:24.404
and, like, hit on guys,
and it was fun, and...

18:24.682 --> 18:25.694
You know, but now...

18:25.719 --> 18:27.721
Yeah. I mean, we've changed.

18:27.746 --> 18:29.502
- Yeah.
- You're a farmer.

18:29.527 --> 18:30.852
I'm growing up.

18:30.877 --> 18:33.109
I'm getting married to a
guy 20 years older than me.

18:33.134 --> 18:34.467
- Yeah.
- Wow. 20... 20 years?

18:34.492 --> 18:36.710
Yeah. I love it.

18:36.754 --> 18:38.718
I actually wish he was older, like Rudy.

18:38.743 --> 18:40.609
- Sure.
- Rudy's a smoke-show,

18:40.634 --> 18:41.883
and I want a puff.

18:41.908 --> 18:43.156
Experience.

18:43.181 --> 18:47.320
I mean, I feel like just because
we change doesn't mean...

18:47.345 --> 18:50.586
you know,
we can't still be friends, right?

18:50.611 --> 18:53.286
Look, remember
that night right before you left,

18:53.311 --> 18:55.240
- and we went out all night?
- Yes.

18:55.265 --> 18:57.459
- And then we ended up at, um...
- Up at the Broadway Diner.

18:57.483 --> 18:59.022
Yes. Oh, my God, and the waiter thought

18:59.046 --> 19:00.725
you were trying to hit on him,
which you were.

19:00.749 --> 19:02.030
- Yes. I was. Totally.
- You know?

19:02.054 --> 19:04.061
- And I was like, "You should"...
- Oh, okay. Pretend I'm not here. Yeah.

19:04.085 --> 19:05.771
- Yeah. Okay.
- He's very good like that.

19:05.796 --> 19:06.796
Okay.

19:06.821 --> 19:09.216
That was my favorite part
about going out with you.

19:09.241 --> 19:11.372
It wasn't the long nights.

19:11.397 --> 19:13.138
It was the breakfast the next day.

19:13.163 --> 19:15.669
It's the breakfast the next day!

19:15.694 --> 19:18.625
- I love you so much, breakfast!
- Breakfast!

19:18.650 --> 19:20.904
- Aww!
- Ow, ow. Okay.

19:20.929 --> 19:22.053
- Love you so much.
- I love you, too.

19:22.077 --> 19:24.021
It's just, my shoulder's
getting a little...

19:24.794 --> 19:26.186
... thrown out. Okay.

19:26.211 --> 19:27.212
- That was beautiful.
- Sorry.

19:27.236 --> 19:29.802
Alright, you're free to go,
and the wedding is back on.

19:29.827 --> 19:31.294
- Ah!
- Oh, look at that.

19:31.319 --> 19:32.624
Connie, thank you.

19:32.649 --> 19:33.779
Look what I got.

19:34.319 --> 19:35.693
Great.

19:35.718 --> 19:37.170
- Why does Daddy not like him?
- It's a little...

19:37.194 --> 19:39.100
You know what I mean?
It's a little hard to pin down...

19:39.124 --> 19:40.655
- Sure...
- but I think it's because he got caught

19:40.679 --> 19:42.812
low-key maybe embezzling some money.

19:42.837 --> 19:44.756
- What? Lars did?
- Not, like, real embezzlement.

19:44.780 --> 19:46.428
- What, like... What...
- But, like, embezzlement-adjacent...

19:46.452 --> 19:49.411
Thought you might
want a hearty breakfast.

19:49.436 --> 19:51.308
Oh, my God! Breakfast!

19:52.608 --> 19:54.381
- Mike, thank you so much.
- No, literally, this is so good.

19:54.405 --> 19:55.905
- Thank you. You saved my wedding.
- I love this.

19:55.929 --> 19:58.106
- I'm obsessed with you.
- I wouldn't let a wall of fire

19:58.130 --> 19:59.958
stand between you and
this embezzler, so...

19:59.983 --> 20:01.412
- Okay. Thanks...
- ... the honor's mine.

20:01.436 --> 20:02.480
What did he embezzle?

20:02.505 --> 20:04.372
Well, Bernie Madoff was his mentor.

20:04.397 --> 20:05.380
Oh, wow.

20:05.405 --> 20:07.625
But Bernie was actually really nice.

20:09.400 --> 20:10.749
Ow!

20:16.052 --> 20:17.216
Hey, Clara.

20:17.241 --> 20:19.951
No, n-n-n-not so, so, so, so, so loud.

20:20.340 --> 20:22.044
So, so, so loud.

20:23.499 --> 20:25.482
Don't do that. Don't do that.

20:28.132 --> 20:29.785
Oh. If you...

20:30.670 --> 20:33.099
No, no. Don't even try. It's impossible.

20:33.124 --> 20:34.580
Doesn't even matter how strong you are.

20:34.604 --> 20:36.044
There's just... There's just no way.

20:38.703 --> 20:40.974
How did you...

20:40.999 --> 20:44.622
I want you to pick me up and
hold me like a baby kangaroo.

20:54.319 --> 20:56.062
That's pretty cool.

